Selected Work

DTC Tech Wearable Product Launch

NextSense Smartbuds: Commercial Launch

As the world's first truly wireless EEG-sensing earbuds, Smartbuds brought clinical-grade brain monitoring out of the lab and into a form people already wear every day. We led the market entry and commercial debut by sharpening the story: this wasn't another device that tracks sleep and delivers a score. It was closed-loop neurotechnology that listens to the brain in milliseconds and responds. The launch narrative cut through a $585B sleep economy saturated with passive trackers by reframing sleep as something you can actively influence, not just measure. By translating six-sensor EEG data and real-time audio stimulation into a clear, consumer-facing promise: deeper sleep, driven at the source. We positioned Smartbuds as a category-defining shift from monitoring to intervention, and established a new frontier in brain-responsive wearables.

Let's Talk Menopause: Non-Profit Advocacy Campaign

Strategically executed media outreach for the "Unboxing Menopause" campaign, a pivotal movement that drove the FDA's landmark decision to remove "black box" warnings on key hormone therapy products. By positioning the organization's experts at the center of the national conversation, the campaign successfully dismantled long-standing taboos and influenced systemic changes in menopause care policy.

Clinic Opening

Biograph: NYC Luxury Preventive Health Clinic Opening

When Biograph emerged from stealth, the opportunity was to introduce more than a clinicit was to define a new category of ultra-luxury preventive health. Offering comprehensive longevity diagnostics and deeply personalized health optimization, Biograph required a launch strategy as considered and precise as its model of care. Working within strict messaging parameters and a deliberately limited digital footprint, we crafted a tightly controlled communications rollout designed to build intrigue while protecting the brand's exclusivity. Rather than positioning Biograph as a medical destination, we shaped a narrative that lived at the intersection of design, lifestyle, wellness, and health. Through carefully orchestrated on-site media immersions and private previews, we ensured journalists experienced the diagnostics journey firsthand. The result was coverage that captured not just the science, but the ambition behind itto establish Biograph as a new benchmark in elevated, personalized longevity care.

Built Agency Offshore Analyst Program: Scaled from 1 to 20

About

With 3+ years of experience in public relations and marketing, I specialize in executive, consumer, and corporate communications across tech, health, and innovation sectors.

My approach combines data-driven insights with strategic storytelling, creating integrated campaigns that drive measurable results. From award submissions to media relations, I bring both analytical rigor and creative execution to every project.

I've had the privilege of working with leading brands like 23andMe, L'Oreal, and numerous health tech startups, consistently delivering campaigns that exceed client expectations. I hold an M.S. in Strategic Communications from Columbia University and a B.A. in Applied Psychology & Media from New York University.
